1
00:00:18,770 --> 00:00:22,190
♪The evening breeze swirls in the moonlight♪

2
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:26,050
♪Falls on the corners of your mouth♪

3
00:00:26,350 --> 00:00:28,780
♪With a shy smile on your face♪

4
00:00:29,120 --> 00:00:31,770
♪Who should speak first♪

5
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:37,240
♪Maybe I can be a bit noisy♪

6
00:00:37,810 --> 00:00:41,160
♪Don't want the atmosphere to get boring♪

7
00:00:41,420 --> 00:00:44,000
♪Love is quite wonderful♪

8
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:47,350
♪I like you but don't dare to tell you♪

9
00:00:47,820 --> 00:00:51,890
♪Oh, you are the shooting star
breaking into the night sky♪

10
00:00:52,050 --> 00:00:55,430
♪Listen to the sound of the heart♪

11
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:59,290
♪Encounter you at the right time♪

12
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:02,830
♪Accompanied by courage♪

13
00:01:03,030 --> 00:01:07,090
♪Oh, love needs no explanation♪

14
00:01:07,310 --> 00:01:10,700
♪You are the meaning I strive for♪

15
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:14,600
♪About your tomorrow and mood♪

16
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:18,070
♪Will slowly be occupied by me♪

17
00:01:18,270 --> 00:01:22,240
♪Oh love, blame you for not understanding♪

18
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:27,490
♪I just want to come with true love for you♪

19
00:01:27,710 --> 00:01:31,390
♪Enough anticipation♪

20
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:34,420
♪Starlight falls into the arms♪

21
00:01:34,420 --> 00:01:36,660
=Treasures Around=

22
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:39,700
=Episode 20=

23
00:01:40,820 --> 00:01:43,460
(Peace and Tranquility)

24
00:02:10,410 --> 00:02:13,040
I have a request.

25
00:02:14,450 --> 00:02:16,410
I've been in the house

26
00:02:17,130 --> 00:02:19,360
serving the madam for over ten years.

27
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,170
The madam rises at 5 am

28
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:23,850
and sleeps at 9 pm.

29
00:02:25,010 --> 00:02:26,450
Though she's old,

30
00:02:26,890 --> 00:02:28,080
she loves sweets.

31
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:32,410
The madam's habits and likes

32
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:36,040
are imprinted in my bones.

33
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:39,760
Now that the madam has passed,

34
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:42,290
I...

35
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:45,250
Aside from sorrow,

36
00:02:45,730 --> 00:02:48,690
I find no purpose in staying here.

37
00:02:49,730 --> 00:02:50,570
Today,

38
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:54,640
I request your permission

39
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,570
to return home

40
00:02:58,170 --> 00:02:59,640
to be a vegetarian and pray

41
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:03,290
for the madam's peaceful next life,

42
00:03:03,450 --> 00:03:05,170
free from suffering.

43
00:03:12,690 --> 00:03:13,530
Ms. Li,

44
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,700
since you've decided,

45
00:03:16,140 --> 00:03:17,340
we won't keep you.

46
00:03:17,940 --> 00:03:18,940
Thank you, Young Master.

47
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,420
Thank you, Ms. Dandan.

48
00:03:24,420 --> 00:03:25,260
Ms. Li,

49
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:27,860
I'll help you pack your things.

50
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:35,500
Thank you, Ms. Shuangshuang.

51
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:00,500
The madam passed suddenly.

52
00:04:00,820 --> 00:04:02,860
You must be very sad.

53
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:04,340
Yes.

54
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,540
With the madam gone,

55
00:04:07,140 --> 00:04:09,860
I feel lost

56
00:04:10,940 --> 00:04:14,140
as if nothing I do has any meaning.

57
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:18,180
Do we know what illness took the madam?

58
00:04:21,620 --> 00:04:22,540
It was tuberculosis,

59
00:04:25,060 --> 00:04:26,300
an old ailment.

60
00:04:33,860 --> 00:04:34,900
It's the aconite herb.

61
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:36,340
If carefully prepared,

62
00:04:36,660 --> 00:04:37,540
it can kill people

63
00:04:37,980 --> 00:04:39,300
within half a day.

64
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:54,540
Thank you for taking care of the madam.

65
00:04:54,860 --> 00:04:56,660
I hope you live peacefully

66
00:04:57,060 --> 00:04:58,460
after leaving here.

67
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:03,980
Thank you, Ms. Shuangshuang.

68
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:32,780
Oh, no. Ms. Li has fainted!

69
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:49,620
Dandan.

70
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:53,300
What's happening?

71
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:54,460
She was fine just now.

72
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:56,100
I was just helping her pack.

73
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,420
She was ready to leave

74
00:05:57,660 --> 00:05:58,980
but suddenly collapsed.

75
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:01,780
Liu, go get a doctor!

76
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:02,900
Alright.

77
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,420
Check her belongings

78
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:08,900
for any emergency medicine.

79
00:06:17,540 --> 00:06:18,380
This...

80
00:06:23,660 --> 00:06:24,540
This is the aconite herb.

81
00:06:24,660 --> 00:06:25,740
It contains aconitine,

82
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:27,300
which can numb the nerves.

83
00:06:27,790 --> 00:06:29,850
It can cause rapid heartbeat,

84
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:32,630
a drop in body temperature, and even death.

85
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:37,220
Why would Ms. Li carry such a thing?

86
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:39,740
Do you remember

87
00:06:39,860 --> 00:06:42,100
the bowl of soup by the madam's bed?

88
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:49,300
Ms. Li made that soup herself.

89
00:06:50,780 --> 00:06:51,660
Are you saying

90
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:55,780
Ms. Li killed the madam?

91
00:06:57,980 --> 00:06:58,820
Impossible.

92
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:01,220
Ms. Li served the madam for years,

93
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:03,060
always loyal.

94
00:07:03,340 --> 00:07:04,340
The doctor said

95
00:07:04,460 --> 00:07:05,980
it was an old ailment.

96
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:07,980
Spare me!

97
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:10,100
Spare me, please!

98
00:07:11,420 --> 00:07:12,260
It was her!

99
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:14,100
She poisoned the madam!

100
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:20,620
This wicked woman!

101
00:07:20,780 --> 00:07:21,900
She forced me to do it.

102
00:07:22,220 --> 00:07:23,340
If I didn't obey,

103
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:24,780
she'd have me killed.

104
00:07:24,780 --> 00:07:26,540
I had no choice!

105
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:28,220
But as a doctor,

106
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:29,860
I failed to save lives

107
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:31,220
and instead caused death.

108
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,620
I can't live without the guilt.

109
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,900
The madam had no severe illness.

110
00:07:37,220 --> 00:07:38,300
She died

111
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,860
because of the colorless, tasteless

112
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:41,620
aconite herb in her soup.

113
00:07:41,660 --> 00:07:42,500
You...

114
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:47,820
Why?

115
00:07:49,620 --> 00:07:50,460
How could you?

116
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:56,380
Why?

117
00:07:58,460 --> 00:08:00,340
She treated you so well.

118
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:02,740
Why did you harm her?

119
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:18,780
Treated me well?

120
00:08:21,420 --> 00:08:23,340
I served her carefully

121
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:25,900
day and night for decades.

122
00:08:26,860 --> 00:08:27,740
And what was I to her?

123
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,660
Just a dog.

124
00:08:31,860 --> 00:08:33,540
Why would I want to kill her?

125
00:08:34,940 --> 00:08:37,580
I've wanted her dead for years.

126
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:38,740
Shut up.

127
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:47,900
Liu,

128
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:49,740
report this to the authorities.

129
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:50,900
Alright.

130
00:08:52,420 --> 00:08:53,260
Go.

131
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,500
I was with the madam that day.

132
00:08:57,140 --> 00:08:58,300
Ms. Li made the lotus root soup

133
00:08:58,780 --> 00:09:00,420
for the young master

134
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:01,780
and Ms. Dandan.

135
00:09:02,540 --> 00:09:04,580
The madam said Ophiopogon is cold by nature,

136
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:05,900
not suitable for you,

137
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:08,180
so she took it herself.

138
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:12,900
So that day,

139
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:16,060
you meant to harm me and the young master.

140
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:18,900
We have no grudge.

141
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:20,820
Why would you harm me?

142
00:09:22,180 --> 00:09:24,140
Who put you up to this?

143
00:09:24,820 --> 00:09:25,660
Speak!

144
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,140
That's right.

145
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:36,780
I wanted you dead.

146
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:39,580
I wanted all of you dead.

147
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:43,420
Do I need someone to put me up to this?

148
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:45,940
I was jealous and angry.

149
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:48,020
I hated seeing you all happy,

150
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:49,900
ignoring the servants.

151
00:09:50,780 --> 00:09:52,420
I wanted

152
00:09:52,540 --> 00:09:54,660
you privileged people

153
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:57,140
to taste pain too.

154
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:10,660
(Wang Jiu,)

155
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:15,300
(I can't wait for you any longer.)

156
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:19,540
(In the next life,)

157
00:10:20,540 --> 00:10:22,420
(you must marry me.)

158
00:10:37,860 --> 00:10:39,940
(Fine Gold and Good Jade)

159
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:45,820
What's wrong?

160
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:47,020
Ms. Li is dead.

161
00:10:48,420 --> 00:10:49,500
I'm sure.

162
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:54,740
Shopkeeper.

163
00:10:55,910 --> 00:10:56,770
I'll check again.

164
00:10:56,780 --> 00:10:58,660
Get out.

165
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:35,820
As long as you stand up again,

166
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,700
Qipei Pavilion will prosper sooner or later.

167
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:40,300
I have confidence in you.

168
00:11:41,060 --> 00:11:41,900
Pei.

169
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:44,020
Mother.

170
00:11:45,260 --> 00:11:46,100
Pei.

171
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:47,540
You're back.

172
00:11:59,020 --> 00:11:59,860
Pei.

173
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:04,780
You can't go anywhere until you eat properly.

174
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:12,620
Pei!

175
00:12:13,060 --> 00:12:13,900
Pei!

176
00:12:14,820 --> 00:12:15,780
You brat.

177
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:17,700
Finish your meal before you go.

178
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:26,060
Pei, do you want to carve jade?

179
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:27,540
Shh.

180
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:28,660
Quiet.

181
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:29,980
What?

182
00:12:30,420 --> 00:12:31,940
I'm fishing.

183
00:12:33,780 --> 00:12:36,020
I asked if you wanted to carve jade.

184
00:12:36,180 --> 00:12:37,660
I'm fishing!

185
00:12:37,780 --> 00:12:38,660
Carve jade.

186
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:40,300
I'm fishing!

187
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:41,560
You brat. Fine.

188
00:12:41,580 --> 00:12:42,220
Just wait.

189
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:43,540
- What are you doing?
- Are you still fishing?

190
00:12:43,540 --> 00:12:44,680
- What are you doing?
- You...

191
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,600
Are you pointing at me? What are you doing?

192
00:12:47,060 --> 00:12:47,900
Put it down.

193
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:49,700
- I won't.
- Put it down.

194
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:50,580
I won't.

195
00:12:50,580 --> 00:12:52,180
You brat, come here!

196
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:53,020
No.

197
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,140
Why are you going to Flower Pavilion?

198
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:56,300
To squander your fortune, of course.

199
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:57,140
What else?

200
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:58,160
You unfilial son.

201
00:12:58,420 --> 00:12:59,600
You're driving me mad.

202
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:01,180
Look at you, all grown up,

203
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:02,760
still so irresponsible.

204
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:04,160
Stop right there!

205
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:05,520
Stop!

206
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,120
I...

207
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:19,240
I don't have a mother anymore.

208
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:24,000
Why?

209
00:14:26,380 --> 00:14:27,640
I don't have a mother anymore.

210
00:14:28,180 --> 00:14:30,160
I don't have a mother anymore.

211
00:14:46,820 --> 00:14:47,680
Pei Pei,

212
00:14:49,380 --> 00:14:53,280
The madam was the best mother in the world.

213
00:14:53,780 --> 00:14:57,360
You've made her proud.

214
00:15:22,780 --> 00:15:23,620
Here.

215
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:32,520
For you,

216
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:35,120
I can be your spy in the Pei family.

217
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,920
To help you achieve your great plans,

218
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:39,760
I'm willing to do anything.

219
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:41,920
Guixiang.

220
00:15:42,950 --> 00:15:44,000
I'm sorry to put you through this.

221
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:51,600
You never minded my background as a maid,

222
00:15:52,540 --> 00:15:53,780
and you were the first

223
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:55,640
to make me a promise in this world.

224
00:15:55,940 --> 00:15:58,600
What does a little hardship matter?

225
00:16:12,020 --> 00:16:12,860
Guixiang,

226
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:15,280
I never imagined

227
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:17,640
you'd sacrifice your life

228
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:20,040
to protect me.

229
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:23,640
I'm sorry.

230
00:16:27,180 --> 00:16:28,240
But don't worry.

231
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:31,120
I will avenge you.

232
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:32,640
The Pei family.

233
00:16:33,420 --> 00:16:35,280
I won't let them go.

234
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,480
Who are you burning paper for?

235
00:16:48,660 --> 00:16:49,500
It's so late.

236
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:50,940
Why are you still awake?

237
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:53,040
I'm asking you who you're doing this for.

238
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:56,360
It can't be Madam Pei, can it?

239
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:02,360
Could it be...?

240
00:17:04,260 --> 00:17:05,840
Yes, it's her.

241
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,740
Where do you think I've been getting

242
00:17:07,740 --> 00:17:09,860
the latest news and designs from Qipei Pavilion

243
00:17:09,860 --> 00:17:11,080
all these years?

244
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,560
My plan was

245
00:17:12,820 --> 00:17:14,620
to kill Pei Pei and Shan Dandan,

246
00:17:14,620 --> 00:17:15,960
the two stumbling blocks.

247
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:18,940
But that old fox

248
00:17:18,940 --> 00:17:20,040
died first.

249
00:17:21,860 --> 00:17:22,700
It's just

250
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:24,920
a pity for my Guixiang.

251
00:17:26,580 --> 00:17:27,540
Are you mad?

252
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:29,040
How could you kill someone?

253
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:31,800
What else could I do?

254
00:17:32,620 --> 00:17:34,540
Watch our hundred-year legacy be destroyed?

255
00:17:34,540 --> 00:17:35,400
So what?

256
00:17:36,300 --> 00:17:37,300
Don't we have strength?

257
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:38,360
Can't we start over?

258
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:39,780
But your hands are stained with blood,

259
00:17:39,780 --> 00:17:41,880
involved in murder. Can you wash it clean?

260
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:43,300
Who do you think you killed?

261
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:44,580
Madam Pei!

262
00:17:44,580 --> 00:17:45,820
The madam of Qipei Pavilion.

263
00:17:45,820 --> 00:17:47,800
How can you speak so lightly?

264
00:17:48,260 --> 00:17:49,100
Fool.

265
00:17:49,780 --> 00:17:51,120
Starting over?

266
00:17:51,540 --> 00:17:52,980
You make it sound so easy.

267
00:17:52,980 --> 00:17:54,320
With what will we start over?

268
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:55,480
Is there still time?

269
00:17:55,740 --> 00:17:56,720
Is there still a chance?

270
00:18:08,940 --> 00:18:09,960
Jue,

271
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:12,880
fate has placed a great responsibility on us.

272
00:18:13,540 --> 00:18:15,060
It has come to this.

273
00:18:15,060 --> 00:18:16,880
We have no way back now.

274
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:18,800
I don't want this either.

275
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:20,160
But now,

276
00:18:20,620 --> 00:18:22,440
Guixiang's life is lost.

277
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:24,240
No matter what,

278
00:18:24,940 --> 00:18:27,080
I'll fight them to the death.

279
00:18:35,060 --> 00:18:35,960
Come with me.

280
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:01,320
Why is there a secret room?

281
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:03,600
Come in.

282
00:19:14,100 --> 00:19:15,480
How could there be a dungeon?

283
00:19:15,860 --> 00:19:17,600
I never knew all these years.

284
00:19:17,820 --> 00:19:18,660
Who...

285
00:19:19,380 --> 00:19:20,440
Who is this?

286
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:26,180
(Pei Chufeng, Qipei Pavilion)

287
00:19:26,220 --> 00:19:27,640
Don't hit me.

288
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:30,400
I'll paint.

289
00:19:34,870 --> 00:19:35,740
This...

290
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:38,800
This is Pei Pei's biological father,

291
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:40,440
Pei Chufeng.

292
00:19:43,580 --> 00:19:44,560
Pei Chufeng?

293
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:47,380
This...

294
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:49,240
What on earth is going on?

295
00:19:51,780 --> 00:19:52,920
At this point,

296
00:19:53,460 --> 00:19:54,640
I won't hide it from you anymore.

297
00:19:55,060 --> 00:19:56,400
When you were young,

298
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:59,600
Qipei Pavilion's quality and craftsmanship

299
00:19:59,820 --> 00:20:01,600
always overshadowed us,

300
00:20:01,820 --> 00:20:03,880
making your father unable to lift his head,

301
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:05,790
until the Emperor

302
00:20:05,790 --> 00:20:07,580
(Guard Zhao, Qipei Pavilion)
wanted the Moonlight Crown.

303
00:20:07,580 --> 00:20:09,020
The City Lord appointed

304
00:20:09,020 --> 00:20:11,240
this old guy as the chief designer.

305
00:20:11,780 --> 00:20:14,680
Your father had no choice
but to steal the treasure.

306
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:15,980
There's an assassin!

307
00:20:51,260 --> 00:20:52,120
Who are you?

308
00:20:52,340 --> 00:20:53,440
Hand over the Crown.

309
00:21:19,660 --> 00:21:21,540
(Shan Jingtian, a warrior)

310
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:22,580
Wang Jiu!

311
00:21:22,580 --> 00:21:23,560
Shan Jingtian.

312
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:25,400
Give me the Crown.

313
00:21:26,100 --> 00:21:27,300
We agreed that day.

314
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:28,640
I would get the Crown for you.

315
00:21:29,140 --> 00:21:30,040
You get the Crown,

316
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:31,940
and I get the water amber on it

317
00:21:31,940 --> 00:21:33,960
for my wife's illness.

318
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:36,080
What are you doing now?

319
00:21:37,980 --> 00:21:39,860
Using water amber as medicine

320
00:21:39,860 --> 00:21:41,040
to treat all diseases.

321
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:42,980
You really believe that?

322
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:44,560
Such an ignorant fool.

323
00:21:44,690 --> 00:21:45,540
You...

324
00:21:45,540 --> 00:21:47,980
I valued you and hired you to steal the Crown.

325
00:21:47,980 --> 00:21:49,460
Now that I have the Crown,

326
00:21:49,460 --> 00:21:50,500
you should go to the afterlife.

327
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:51,840
Didn't you see this coming?

328
00:21:52,220 --> 00:21:54,860
Yes. Water amber is precious,

329
00:21:54,860 --> 00:21:56,780
but there are countless treasures in the world.

330
00:21:56,780 --> 00:21:58,540
The real value is in the amazing craftsmanship

331
00:21:58,540 --> 00:21:59,980
of the Crown.

332
00:21:59,980 --> 00:22:01,600
You wouldn't understand.

333
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:04,720
Think about it as a ghost in the afterlife.

334
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,340
Sir,

335
00:22:06,980 --> 00:22:08,160
I was deceived

336
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,360
into stealing your precious treasure.

337
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:13,360
Today, I'll sacrifice my life

338
00:22:13,740 --> 00:22:15,360
to return it to its rightful owner.

339
00:22:16,380 --> 00:22:19,080
At that time, Qipei Pavilion
couldn't produce the Crown.

340
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:20,560
So, we seized

341
00:22:21,060 --> 00:22:23,080
the opportunity

342
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:26,240
and presented our prepared backup crown.

343
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:30,920
From then on, our reputation soared nationwide.

344
00:22:31,620 --> 00:22:33,840
So, Suyu Pavilion became what it is today.

345
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:36,240
For so many years,

346
00:22:37,140 --> 00:22:40,200
I only knew there was a drawing
of the Crown in our house.

347
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:41,980
Come here.

348
00:23:29,540 --> 00:23:31,560
(I'll kill you together.)

349
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:40,360
Careful! It's poison!

350
00:23:47,020 --> 00:23:47,880
You go first.

351
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:49,880
I entrust my daughter to you.

352
00:23:50,140 --> 00:23:52,040
I need to get the remaining Crown.

353
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,840
Take good care of her for me.

354
00:24:37,540 --> 00:24:40,720
Actually, we've always had the Crown.

355
00:24:41,260 --> 00:24:42,960
But one half

356
00:24:43,300 --> 00:24:45,160
was taken by that thief.

357
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:47,300
Now, even with our skills,

358
00:24:47,300 --> 00:24:48,880
we can't master its craftsmanship.

359
00:24:49,460 --> 00:24:51,140
Remember when your father

360
00:24:51,140 --> 00:24:52,840
taught you some techniques,

361
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:54,800
but you couldn't master them?

362
00:24:57,580 --> 00:24:59,200
Those were the techniques from the Crown.

363
00:24:59,780 --> 00:25:00,720
So,

364
00:25:01,580 --> 00:25:02,920
because I couldn't master them,

365
00:25:04,100 --> 00:25:05,480
you broke

366
00:25:06,300 --> 00:25:07,640
Pei Pei's hand?

367
00:25:08,100 --> 00:25:08,960
Yes.

368
00:25:10,820 --> 00:25:12,380
After dealing with the old,

369
00:25:12,380 --> 00:25:14,620
the young one emerged to fight with you.

370
00:25:14,620 --> 00:25:16,400
How could your father let them succeed?

371
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:25,800
(It's your fault for outshining Jue.)

372
00:25:26,540 --> 00:25:29,640
(Your talent is your fault.)

373
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:33,600
So, all these years,

374
00:25:34,540 --> 00:25:36,160
I never truly won against him.

375
00:25:38,260 --> 00:25:39,840
I was just a clown,

376
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:42,440
feeling proud for years.

377
00:25:43,220 --> 00:25:45,440
The one who laughs last is the true winner.

378
00:25:46,260 --> 00:25:47,120
Jue,

379
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:49,880
don't blame me and your father
for being ruthless.

380
00:25:50,620 --> 00:25:52,580
The world's contests are fatal.

381
00:25:52,580 --> 00:25:54,240
Only the victor can rule.

382
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:55,720
Look at Pei Pei.

383
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,880
As soon as he gained the raw stone,

384
00:25:58,460 --> 00:26:00,880
he was eager to destroy us.

385
00:26:07,060 --> 00:26:08,360
When the Crown was lost,

386
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:09,980
your father spread rumors,

387
00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:12,210
making people suspect he stole it himself.

388
00:26:12,210 --> 00:26:13,640
The City Lord investigated him three times,

389
00:26:14,100 --> 00:26:16,020
making him live in constant fear,

390
00:26:16,020 --> 00:26:18,160
afraid to let his son shine.

391
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:19,540
But Pei Pei

392
00:26:19,540 --> 00:26:21,880
glanced at the Crown's dissection diagram

393
00:26:22,380 --> 00:26:23,980
and could mimic its techniques

394
00:26:23,980 --> 00:26:25,480
to seventy percent.

