(The melting technique of South Bead
and gold on the Crown.)

453
00:30:33,300 --> 00:30:34,380
Shuangshuang,

454
00:30:34,980 --> 00:30:36,740
I was framed.

455
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:39,380
I failed your mother,

456
00:30:40,140 --> 00:30:42,140
and I failed you.

457
00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:56,060
Shuangshuang,

458
00:30:58,380 --> 00:30:59,540
you didn't go to the workshop?

459
00:31:03,500 --> 00:31:04,340
No.

460
00:31:05,500 --> 00:31:06,540
What's wrong?

461
00:31:07,020 --> 00:31:09,300
I want to talk to Mr. Pei alone.

462
00:31:09,620 --> 00:31:10,740
Is that alright?

463
00:31:12,620 --> 00:31:13,460
Sure.

464
00:31:14,170 --> 00:31:16,880
You two talk. I'll make some pastries.

465
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:26,780
What do you want to discuss?

466
00:31:27,460 --> 00:31:28,300
You made this?

467
00:31:28,780 --> 00:31:29,620
Yes.

468
00:31:29,660 --> 00:31:31,500
A small gift for Dandan.

469
00:31:33,020 --> 00:31:35,260
For the lost techniques of the Moonlight Crown,

470
00:31:35,500 --> 00:31:37,900
whether it's gold and silver inlay,
filigree carving,

471
00:31:37,900 --> 00:31:39,300
or hollow vertical carving,

472
00:31:39,300 --> 00:31:41,300
you've mastered them all.

473
00:31:41,300 --> 00:31:42,820
Who taught you?

474
00:31:43,180 --> 00:31:46,060
My father participated
in the design of the Crown.

475
00:31:47,060 --> 00:31:48,780
He was familiar with many techniques.

476
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:50,060
When I was young,

477
00:31:50,060 --> 00:31:51,900
I was lucky to see the actual Crown.

478
00:31:51,900 --> 00:31:53,740
Plus, my father taught me,

479
00:31:53,740 --> 00:31:54,780
so I know a bit.

